  <steps>
    <step num="0">Heat the oil in a large sauce pan over a medium heat. </step>
    <step num="1">Add the ribs and sear until all sides turn golden brown. </step>
    <step num="2">Add in all the seasoning. </step>
    <step num="3">Bring the liquid to a boil, reduce heat, and cover. Simmer the ribs for an hour to 90 minutes. Until the ribs become really tender. </step>
    <step num="4">Once the ribs are cooked remove lid and reduce the sauce for 5 minutes. </step>
    <step num="5">Serve drizzled with sauce. </step>
    <step num="6">Enjoy! </step>
